  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714657061744-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714657061744-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714657061744-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714657061744-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714657061744-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> your <strong>honey</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>Dijon</strong> <strong>mustard </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>cracked</strong> <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>lemon & pepper</strong> <strong>marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714657066775-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714657066775-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714657066775-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714657066775-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714657066775-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a clean chopping board</p><p>Slice through the thickest part of the chicken, being careful not to cut all the way through to the other side and open it out like a book</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling</strong> <strong>film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin</strong> until you have an even thickness – this is your <strong>butterflied chicken</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>butterflied</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> to the marinade, give everything a good mix up and set aside to marinate</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714657071831-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714657071831-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
